Review Text.1: This is a nice vegan cafe in Vile Parle West at Juhu!u003cbr/>- Menu: They have some very unique options, which are quite different from other cafesu003cbr/>- Our order (for 4): Berry love smoothie bowl, Avocado Bruschetta, Seek the Carbs, 1 Cappuccino, 1 Hazelnut Cappucino, 1 Mochau003cbr/>- Food quality: very good, loved the smoothie bowl and the avocado bruschetta was very freshu003cbr/>- Food quantity: Above order was sufficient for 4 of us for a brunch mealu003cbr/>- Wait time: quick service, took only 10-15 minutes for orders to start rolling inu003cbr/>- Pricing: They levy 10% service chargeu003cbr/>- What we liked: very good ambience, prompt service, freshly prepared dishes, valet service was availableu003cbr/>- Additional things to keep in mind: This is a small cafe, so it gets filled up quickly during rush hours

Review Text.31: I recently visited this cafe and I have to say, I was thoroughly impressed! From the moment I walked in, I was greeted with a warm smile and welcoming atmosphere. The staff were all friendly and attentive, and the owner even took the time to come over and personally greet people and thank them for coming in.u003cbr/>u003cbr/>The food was absolutely delicious. I ordered a sweet potato starter and it was fresh, flavorful and made with high-quality ingredients. They also had a great selection of smoothies which was also fresh and baked goods, all of which looked amazing.u003cbr/>u003cbr/>But what really stood out to me was the exceptional service. Despite the busy lunch rush, the staff remained cheerful, attentive and accommodating to all of their customers. Everyone seemed genuinely happy to be working there, and it showed in the way they treated their customers. The interior of the restaurant too, gives out alot of positive and calm vibes. u003cbr/>u003cbr/>Overall, I would recommend this cafe to anyone looking for delicious food and exceptional service. The warm and welcoming atmosphere, combined with the delicious food and friendly staff, make this a must-visit spot for anyone looking for a great dining experience.

Review Text.72: I recently had the misfortune of visiting Earth cafe, and I can confidently say that it was one of the most disappointing dining experiences I've ever had. From the exorbitant prices to the lackluster food, this café failed to deliver on every front.u003cbr/>Let's start with the pricing. I understand that some establishments charge a premium for quality, but [Café Name] took it to a whole new level. The menu boasted lofty prices that would lead you to expect a culinary masterpiece, but what I received was far from it. It felt like a slap in the face to pay such exorbitant amounts for what turned out to be subpar dishes.u003cbr/>Speaking of the food, it was nothing short of disappointing. I ordered their supposedly signature dish, but it arrived looking like a sad, underwhelming imitation of what was described on the menu. The presentation lacked creativity, and the flavors were completely underwhelming. The ingredients seemed cheap, and it felt like the kitchen staff had no passion or skill when it came to preparing the dishes. The food lacked seasoning, tasted bland, and left me craving something more satisfying.u003cbr/>To make matters worse, the portion sizes were laughably small for the prices charged. I left the café feeling unsatisfied and had to find an alternative place to appease my hunger. It's mind-boggling that Earth Cafe believes it can get away with serving tiny portions and charging an arm and a leg for them.u003cbr/>u003cbr/>All in all, I cannot recommend Earth Cafe to anyone. The combination of sky-high prices, subpar food, and lackluster service make it a complete disappointment. Save your hard-earned money and seek out other dining options where you can truly enjoy your meal without feeling ripped off.
